ice had cleft palate with rudimentary palatal shelves spaced apart without contact suggesting that the cleft is due to insufficient outgrowth of the shelves (Rice, Spencer-Dene et al. 2004).   100% (n=22) Osr2-IresCre;Smoc/c had a cleft palate. At E14.5 the palatal shelves were underdeveloped and had not grown out to make contact compared to control littermates that had met and initiated fusion. This supports that disruption of SHH signalling impairs palatal shelf outgrowth and can lead to cleft palate (Lan and Jiang 2009)", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:50:26 +0000 2026"}